    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup is anchored by **Daulton Varsho** (72.31) and **Bryson Stott** (68.67), who represent our strongest statistical plays. **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Bradley (xERA 4.45), combining a +11% SP skill advantage with a solid spot in the #2 hole, while **Bryson Stott** is our most efficient play against a tough arm in Gallen; his 13% platoon edge allows him to maintain elite efficiency despite the caliber of the opposition. **Taylor Ward** and **Brendan Donovan** also grade out as high-tier starts, both exceeding 66 points thanks to favorable park factors and high-leverage spots in their respective batting orders.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical hurdles, most notably with **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, whose score of 54.71 is depressed by a daunting matchup against Sale (xERA 2.88). While his pedigree usually dictates a mandatory start, the sheer dominance of the opposing pitcher makes this a marginal play compared to the efficiency of our OF core. The most difficult bench decision involved **Gleyber Torres** (53.98), who fell just shy of the starting cut. While his metrics were respectable, the decision to sit him\u2014along with **Jung Hoo Lee** and **Yainer Diaz**\u2014was driven by the superior dynamic platoon advantages and run-scoring potential inherent in the rest of the lineup. We are also monitoring the status of **Will Smith**, who remains benched due to a brutal matchup against deGrom; protecting our daily game caps is paramount when the math indicates a sub-40 floor. Ensure all eyes remain on the park factors for **Matt Chapman** and **Jeremiah Jackson**, as their high-ceiling park scores are the primary drivers keeping them in the lineup today despite more modest base projections.",
